parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward
accelerates unexpectedly
or the accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the accelerator cable can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle surges forward
or the accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle does not stop when the brakes are applied
or the brake pedal catches on the gas pedal
allowing the engine to rev up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to repair recalled components can lead to continued safety risks, including unintended acceleration and brake failure.
symptoms: Dealerships do not have parts available to conduct recall repairs
or repairs are not performed correctly
leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause the serpentine belt to break, leading to power steering failure, overheating, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The air conditioning compressor locks up
the serpentine belt breaks
the power steering fails
the vehicle overheats
and a loud squealing noise is heard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
coolant leaks
the temperature gauge fluctuates
and white smoke is seen coming from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause the engine to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine
oil spots are seen on the driveway
and a burning smell is noticed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain and tensioner can cause the engine to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The timing chain and tensioner need to be replaced
and a ticking or knocking noise is heard from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine fails to start
the vehicle stalls
no prior warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The engine surges
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
power windows malfunction
loud clicking noise when pressing the button to roll down windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming from underneath the vehicle
vehicle catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire wear and performance issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Tires have no tread
vehicle hesitates or stalls when giving gas
passenger side window makes an awful noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls abruptly when applying throttle from a standstill
no prior warnings.
